The Federal Airports Authority of Nigeria (FAAN) has temporarily closed the Murtala Mohammed International Airport E-Finger departure screening point to carry out some routine maintenance on the screening machines. Mrs Henrietta Yakubu, the General Manager, Corporate Affairs of the authority, disclosed this in a statement on Tuesday in Lagos, NAN reports. Henrietta said the process was part of the airport maintenance and upgrade programme of the authority. “Consequently, all human and cargo movements have been temporarily diverted to the D-Finger screening area until the maintenance and upgrades are completed. “The authority appeals to passengers and other airport users to please bear with us as we hope to reopen the area as soon as possible,” she said.